But the ﬁr and primary occaon did ariſe as followeth;you may remember that I was provi‑ dentially ca among you at Cranbrook at your generall Aembling there July 21. 1652. where you did appoint me with ſome others, to endea‑ vour to give ſatiſfaion touching ſome points in Religion that were queioned by ſome ; to which end and purpoſe we did meet on the x and twen‑ tieth of the ſame moneth at Yalding about the mat‑ ter, which when we were aembled, among o‑ ther things, this fell in as the matter mo in dif‑ ference, viz. falling from Grace: whereupon there was two Potions ated, the one by me, and the other by the other party: the potion ated by me was, That Believers in Chriﬆ may fall away.
